{{nihongo|'''''Bats & Terry'''''|バツ&テリー|Batsu & Teri|lead=yes}} is a Japanese [[manga]] series written and illustrated by [[Yasuichi Oshima]]. It was serialized in [[Kodansha]]'s ''[[Weekly Shōnen Magazine]]'' from 1982 to 1987. ''Batsu & Terī'' received the 1984 [[Kodansha Manga Award]] for the [[shōnen manga|shōnen]] category.<ref name="KodanshaHahn">{{cite web|url=http://www.hahnlibrary.net/comics/awards/kodansha.php|author=Joel Hahn|title=Kodansha Manga Awards |publisher=Comic Book Awards Almanac|access-date=2009-04-04| archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20090410061256/http://www.hahnlibrary.net/comics/awards/kodansha.php| archive-date= 10 April 2009 | url-status= live}}</ref> [[Kodansha]] published the manga's 24 ''[[tankōbon]]'' volumes to December 1987. The manga's license was transferred to [[Ichijinsha]] and was published into four wideban volumes.

The manga was adapted into an animated movie by [[Sunrise (company)|Sunrise]]. Directed by Mitsuko Kase and [[Tetsuro Amino]], the movie was released in Japan on March 14, 1987. A [[VHS]] was released for the movie on April 21, 1987.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.co.jp/gp/product/B00005EEGV/ |title=バツ&テリー [VHS]|date=21 April 1987 |language=ja|access-date=2009-04-04}}</ref>

The manga was adapted into a side-scrolling [[action game]] for the [[Nintendo Entertainment System|Famicom]]. The game was developed and released by Use Corporation on July 22, 1987.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamefaqs.com/console/nes/data/578444.html|title=Bats and Terry|publisher= [[GameFAQs]]|access-date=2008-11-25}}</ref>

==Manga==
[[Kodansha]] published the manga's 24 ''[[tankōbon]]'' volumes to December 1987.<ref>{{cite book|script-title=ja:バツ&テリー 24 (少年マガジンコミックス)|language=ja|id={{ASIN|4063113051|country=jp}}}}</ref> The manga was re-released into 12 ''[[kanzenban]]'' volumes between March 1991 and August 1991.<ref>{{cite book|title=バツ&テリー 1 (KCスペシャル)|language=ja|id={{ASIN|4063055019|country=jp}}}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=バツ&テリー 12 (KCスペシャル)|language=ja|id={{ASIN|4063055124|country=jp}}}}</ref> The manga's license was transferred to [[Ichijinsha]]. Ichijinsha published the manga into four ''[[aizoban]]'' (wide-ban) volumes between July 27, 2008, and November 25, 2008.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.shop.ichijinsha.co.jp/book/booksearch/booksearch_detail.php?i=75802006&TITLE=%A5%D0%A5%C4%A1%F5%A5%C6%A5%EA%A1%BC&WRITER=&ISBN=&CATEGORY=&SALEY=&SALEM=&WORD=&TYPE=like |script-title=ja:バツ&テリー 愛狂抗争編(前) |publisher=[[Ichijinsha]] |language=ja |access-date=2009-07-21 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081023174455/http://www.shop.ichijinsha.co.jp/book/booksearch/booksearch_detail.php?i=75802006 |archive-date=2008-10-23 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.shop.ichijinsha.co.jp/book/booksearch/booksearch_detail.php?i=75802012&TITLE=%A5%D0%A5%C4%A1%F5%A5%C6%A5%EA%A1%BC&WRITER=&ISBN=&CATEGORY=&SALEY=&SALEM=&WORD=&TYPE=like |script-title=ja:バツ&テリー αα死闘編 |publisher=[[Ichijinsha]] |language=ja |access-date=2009-07-21 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081224230146/http://www.shop.ichijinsha.co.jp/book/booksearch/booksearch_detail.php?i=75802012 |archive-date=2008-12-24 }}</ref>

==Game==
The player controls a [[baseball]] [[superhero]] named Batsu (Bats) who must use baseballs to defeat his opponents. Being hit once reverts him to "normal" Terii (Terry), who swats at his opponents using a [[baseball bat]]. Opponents include machinery, humanoids, and animals. Killing opponents while in Terii form results in a larger energy bar.

